latestPosts.caption:
PINK AND GOLD NAILS AND TOES. DEMI WISPY LASHES. SUMMER IS HEREEEEE 
@nail.rituals  @alistclub

I challenge you to lust for life.
Drink more iced mochas and strawberry -infused water, and a little less vodka soda at 4 AM after you’ve danced through your dopamine reserves. Stretch your body like it deserves to be held, even if it’s just a 20-minute bedroom flow while your hair mask sets in. Lift more than just people’s energy—lift heavy, lift soft, lift for that burn that reminds you you’re powerful. Fill your nights with messy notes, dumb Pinterest boards, and deep convos that spiral into 3 AM epiphanies.

Book that weekend Beach trip even if your schedule’s chaotic. Dance at a Swift night, cry in the Uber back, and wake up in a stranger’s T-shirt making eggs like life’s a movie.

Listen when people talk, but listen more when they don’t. Ask questions that don’t have easy answers. Pick up The Book Thief and remember that words mean things.

Use your time like it’s a love letter to your future self. Take long Sunday showers. Romanticize your to-do list.

I challenge you to lust for life—not just exist with a heartbeat and a calendar full of things.
But to wake up and mean it.
To crave life like it’s a warm croissant on a winter afternoon. To chase joy like you’d chase a stupid boy across the city just to steal your hoodie back.

You’re not here to be passive.
You’re here to experience. 
Live with the burning need to Live.
